    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down Beckenham Kent</hi> </placeName>
                    <date>Aug 1. 1877</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am very much obliged to you for your clear account of the cleistogamic flowers of Collomia, together with the dried flowers.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> The case seems to me a very striking and interesting one.</p>
<p>I remain, dear Sir, | Yours faithfully &amp; obliged | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Ludwig had sent CD his description of cleistogamic flowers of <hi rend="italic">Collomia grandiflora</hi> (large-flowered mountain trumpet or phlox) from the <hi rend="italic">Verhandlungen des botanischen Vereins für die Provinz Brandenburg</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_10267.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Ludwig 1876</ref>). CD’s annotated copy of Ludwig’s description is in DAR 133.19: 6. CD added a reference to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_10267.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Ludwig 1876</ref> in the preface to <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9500.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Forms of flowers</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, p. x.</note>
        </div>        
            
